latestPosts.caption:
Cleaned and Organised my home temple as it needed refresh! 🌹🙏🏻 I feel fresh and revived post this major act.🤗
It’s not about how much you have, it’s about how you value whatever you have!🤗♥️🙏🏻
This is the most loved space of my home. I transformed a bookshelf into my home temple when we started our married life in this rented home. Considering the fact that when I will have my own home someday, I will definitely have a dedicated place for home temple and I can reuse this special shelf for some good purpose.🙏🏻

Thanks to each one of you for all the love that you have poured on this space. I feel immensely grateful and blessed to spend time in this place of my house everyday. ♥️
But I believe it’s not us who create space for god, instead it’s god who chooses his own space at our homes which transforms the entire home divine.

latestPosts.caption:
Hello!👋 

Was I missed? Well, thanks to each one of you who checked on me and my whereabouts over dm’s.

Here are some life updates that I have been longing to share:
We got a new house together and i can’t wait to share this journey with you all. However, this achievement is not mine alone— it’s ours as a family. This manifestation couldn’t have been possible without the blessings and support of lord Jagannath, our parents and well wishers. 🙏🏻♥️
I am quite occupied with multiple things since 4-5months and I am still not sorted yet. Shifting, attending family functions, handover of new house, Gruha Pravesh, to and fro travel to my hometown, changes to office projects, interiors and a lot of chaos have been going on in life in the past months. Despite having faced a lot of hurdles and obstacles on this journey, we overcome and stood up stronger.☺️🎉

We had our housewarming ceremony as per the Odia traditional Gruha Pravesh rituals on 25th April 2025 and these are few glimpses from that day. I will be sharing more pictures of that day with rest of my family who were part of this celebration soon. 💝🙏🏻🥰

P.S- The interiors are half the way as of now and we will be shifting to our new house by end of June this year. Meanwhile, I will be sharing few videos and more pictures that I managed to capture during the busiest times of my life. 
I’ll will be taking you all along this journey!♥️

Wearing: pure khaddi georgette bandhej saree
Pic courtesy: @sumanthpxl ☺️

latestPosts.caption:
We are blessed and grateful that goddess maa chose us to be part of the ‘Danda Nacha’ rituals for a day. This impromptu divine favour of Maa kali will always stay close to our hearts.♥️🙏🏻🙌🏻

This video has very few visuals of the rituals which were going on for 24 hours.

AI Overview :

In Ganjam district, Danda Nacha is a centuries-old, ritualistic folk dance and theatrical form, part of the Danda Yatra, a religious festival dedicated to Goddess Rudrakali, involving penance, devotion, and dancers called Danduas who endure hardships like walking on hot sand and burning embers.
